<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-743-157  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 743 157.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MIS Week  July 10 1989 v10 n27 p6(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Computer industry seeks legal vaccine. (for computer viruses)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Hackett, David.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Computer and software makers urge Congress to create legislationthat would make the creation of computer viruses illegal.andO;Legislation has already been proposed which would imposepenalities of up to 15 years imprisonment for persons whoknowingly sabotage computer systems.andP;  Another bill would make it acriminal offense to implant a virus that causes a threat to humanlife or welfare.andP;  A provision of the bill would allow charges tobe filed against the creators of viruses by computer users whowere affected by the crime.andP;  A first time offender could a receivea sentence of 10 years and repeat offenders could receive 20-yearjail terms.andP;  Both bills are likely to be revised by the Senatebefore legislators consider them further.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Computer VirusesComputer HackersLegal IssuesData SecurityUnited States. Congress. SenateComputer CrimesLegislation.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>